description:
The investment seeks to track the investment results of the Dow Jones U.S. Select Investment Services Index composed of U.S. equities in the investment services sector.
 The fund generally invests at least 90% of its assets in securities of the underlying index and in depositary receipts representing securities of the underlying index. The underlying index measures the performance of the investment services sector of the U.S. equity market. The fund may invest the remainder of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents. It is non-diversified.
